          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="section-inner">
        <div class="section-kicker">Safety</div>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Local source analysis with guarded rewrites.</h2>
        <div class="grid-3">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Local AST analysis</h3>
            <p>FlagLint parses local JavaScript and TypeScript source files. It does not execute your application.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>No LaunchDarkly SDK key needed</h3>
            <p>Scan, migrate, and validate operate on source code. They do not need a LaunchDarkly API key or SDK key.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>No source upload</h3>
            <p>The CLI runs locally in your checkout and does not upload application source to a FlagLint service.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="section-inner">
        <div class="section-kicker">CI enforcement</div>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Block direct SDK calls and upload SARIF annotations.</h2>
        <div class="ci-example">
          <div class="proof-card">
            <h3>Blocking workflow</h3>
<pre>name: FlagLint Policy
on: [pull_request]

jobs:
  validate:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    permissions:
      contents: read
      security-events: write
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version: 20
      - run: |
          npx flaglint validate ./src \
            --no-direct-launchdarkly \
            --format sarif \
            --output flaglint-validation.sarif
      - uses: github/codeql-action/upload-sarif@v3
        if: always()
        with:
          sarif_file: flaglint-validation.sarif</pre>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>SARIF annotations</h3>
            <p><code>validate --format sarif</code> emits direct-SDK policy findings using rule id <code>flaglint.direct-launchdarkly</code>. Upload the SARIF file with GitHub Code Scanning so reviewers see exact file and line annotations.</p>
            <p class="note">Do not set <code>continue-on-error: true</code> on the blocking validation step. Use <code>if: always()</code> only on a later SARIF upload step.</p>
            <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/docs/integrations/github-actions">Read GitHub Actions setup</a>
          </div>
